<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="spare-adj">spare <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /speə(r)/    美 /sper/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>不用的；闲置的</strong></h4>
<p>not being used or not needed at the present：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In my house, there are some spare bedrooms.
我家里有几个空房间。</p><footer>北师大② – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m afraid I haven’t got any <strong>spare cash</strong>.
恐怕我手头上没有闲钱。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>备用的；额外的：</strong></h4>
<p>kept in case you need to replace the one you usually use (extra)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>spare parts
备用件</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a spare tire
备用轮胎</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>空闲的：</strong></h4>
<p>time when you are not working (free)：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>In my <strong>spare time</strong>, I read a lot.
在空闲时间里，我读很多书。</p><footer>2011 辽宁</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I haven’t had a <strong>spare moment</strong> this morning.
今天上午我一刻也没闲着。</p></div></div>